<L>__{exterior paul's house sunset}
<A>__{tv news camera pov: of paul, standing on his stoop, as he's interviewed by a well made up female tv reporter (20s) dressed for the cold.}
<C>__{tv reporter}
<D>__{you ready mr. barnell?}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{yes.}
<A>__{the camera man flicks on his light as paul squints.}
<C>__{tv reporter}
<D>__{the police told us what happened, how are you folks holding up?}
<C>__{margaret }
<D>__{paul? who's out there?}
<A>__{paul reaches back, and, as discretely as possible, grabs the door handle to keep margaret from opening it.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{obviously, my wife's very upset...}
<C>__{margaret }
<D>__{paul, the door's stuck!}
<A>__{margaret starts to hammer rhythmically on the door.}
<C>__{paul}
<P>__{(ignoring her)}
<D>__{it's been a tough, you know, when something like this happens you just have to ask yourself...}
<C>__{margaret }
<D>__{who fucked with the fucking door!}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{you can see how stressful it's been, i should really go now. we have to plan a service.}
<A>__{and with that, paul opens his front door and ducks inside, quickly shutting it behind him.}
